<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 21 at 3:01PM PDT  by NWS Hanford</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT WEST CENTRAL MARIPOSA AND
NORTHEASTERN MERCED COUNTIES THROUGH 330 PM PDT...
At 301 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 14
miles northeast of Merced, moving north at 10 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.
This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of west central
Mariposa and northeastern Merced Counties.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
